<div style="padding: 20px;">
    <p style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; color: #1976D2; letter-spacing: 2px;">HNDIT 4232 PROJECT</p>
    <h1>Eduwide Login Portal Project Report</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Framework: Flutter (Dart) | Backend: Firebase (Auth &amp; Firestore) &amp; Cloudinary REST API</p>

    <div class="highlight-box">
        <p><strong>Project Overview:</strong> This report is pre-formatted for submission. You can open this file directly in Microsoft Word and save it as a standard Word Document (.docx) file.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Project Overview &amp; Objectives</h2>
    <p>This project, named <strong>Eduwide</strong> (commercially branded as <strong>EduLK</strong>), is a cross-platform mobile application developed using Flutter. The system serves as a secure, scalable authentication and profile management portal. It incorporates a role-based access control (RBAC) model to distinguish between <strong>Admin</strong> and <strong>User</strong> accounts. Additionally, it integrates with <strong>Cloudinary CDN</strong> for remote media storage, ensuring efficient handling of profile pictures without stressing the primary database.</p>
    
    <h3>Key Objectives:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Implement secure sign-up, sign-in, and password recovery mechanisms using Firebase.</li>
        <li>Enable detailed profile management by linking Firestore documents to Auth accounts.</li>
        <li>Implement UI dispatching based on server-side roles (Admin vs. User).</li>
        <li>Incorporate direct HTTP multipart uploads to Cloudinary storage buckets.</li>
        <li>Add email verification checks that restrict profile actions until the email link is verified.</li>
        <li>Apply custom timezone database localization (Colombo, Sri Lanka).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Technology Stack &amp; Dependencies</h2>
    <p>The application is built on top of the Flutter SDK and utilizes the following verified dependencies from the <code>pubspec.yaml</code> file:</p>
    
